(Buffer append/copy fixed-buffer truncation behavior)

a buffer called "src" is "ABCDEFG".

a buffer called "dst" is 5 bytes in size.
append src to dst.
Print dst's size.
Print dst.
On error print "append overflow".

a buffer called "dst2" is 4 bytes in size.
copy src to dst2.
Print dst2's size.
Print dst2.
On error print "copy overflow".
